Package net.philsprojects.net

Interface Summary
Acceptor An acceptor is a service which handles a set of servers.
Adapter An adapter is anything which can read, write, accept, or connect.
Client A client is created when a pipeline is requested to connect to some server listening on some address OR when a server accepts a client.
ClientFactory A factory which creates a client handled by the given worker and which uses the given pipeline.
ClientListener A listener to the events of a client.
Pipeline TODO set of servers listening with the pipeline, set of clients connected with the pipeline.
Protocol<D> A protocol decodes an object from a ByteReader and encodes an object to a ByteWriter.
ProtocolListener<D> A listener of encoding and decoding errors of a protocol.
Selector A selector assists in proving and managing pools of acceptors and workers.
Server TODO set of clients accepted on the server
ServerFactory A factory which creates a server handled by the given accepter, which uses the given selector and pipeline, and has binded to the given address.
ServerListener  
Worker A worker is a service which handles a set of clients.
 

Class Summary
AbstractClient A basic implementation of a client.
AbstractPipeline A basic implementation of a Pipeline.
AbstractProtocol<D> An abstract implementation of a Protocol that handles basic getters and setters.
AbstractSelector An abstract implementation of a selector.
AbstractServer An abstract implementation of a Server.
ClientListenerAdapter A basic ClientListener which prints all events out to stdout.
ProtocolListenerAdapter<D> A basic ProtocolListener which prints all events to stdout.
ServerListenerAdapter A basic ServerListener which prints all events to stdout.
